To this day, I take advantage of the contacts that I have gained through the contests.
The franchise sale of his hotel helped Lukas Pytloun well for the place of winner of the Best Individual Entrepreneur contest.
Last year’s winner of the Best Individual Entrepreneur competition was 28-year-old entrepreneur Lukas Pytloun.
His adventure to success is like in a movie.
Lukas Pytloun loved to travel.
And abroad, he realized that Liberec lacked a quality hosting site at a reasonable price.
From his savings on what he had earned when working abroad and with the help of a bank loan he bought a small building of 5 apartments half demolished.
Knowing that he was still a student in the second year of graduate school, it was a brave action.
“The relationship between the quality and the price of accommodation in our area made me want to do something,” says Lucas Pytloun.
He began renting the first rebuilt apartment to foreign workers.
He reinvested the profit in the building that he converted into a pension with 54 beds.
Since then, his entrepreneurial activity has allowed him to open in Liberec 4 guest houses, two style restaurants and two hotels with a total capacity of nearly 300 beds of all accommodation categories.
The most comfortable of them was until recently the four-star Pytloun design hotel.
This year there was another one of the same quality.
"We have just signed a contract with a hotel at Ostrova U Tise where we sold our franchise concept and other Pytloun hotel franchise candidates showed up," the number one contractor last year.
"And for the sale of the license for the operation of a large-scale hotel the victory in the competition of the entrepreneur of the year served well," adds Pytloun with gratitude.
The victory brought him more popularity and to be known in Liberec and its surroundings.
“People recognized me on the streets, often congratulated me and, I must say, it was very pleasant,” he recalls.
It recommends participation in this competition to all those who strive to do something.
It is not necessary to win but any opportunity to be visible is good.
He says he is still using his contacts and knowledge that he could not have obtained in any other way.
"With those I met through the contest I started to maintain business relationships regularly.
According to him, the fame related to the success had an impact on the employees as well.
And he's about 70.
“I observe in them above all the loyalty and pride of being committed to something that has been generally recognized.”
“This is by far not the only result of my personal work, but the result of a good work of all of us together.
“Only my name is pushed forward,” says Lucas Pytloun with modesty.
I wish my successor a better year than we had at Farmet.
The euphoria of victory was quickly replaced by the effects of the crisis.
Thanks to the sense of the goal of the winner Farmet has the worst moments behind him.
The one who came to pick up the prize at Slovansky dum for the first place in the competition for the Firm of the Year organized by Vodaphone last year is Karel Zdarsky the owner of the company Farmet.
The jury rewarded the efforts with which it transformed a tool shop in Ceska Skalice into a firm with a turnover of 100 million crowns.
"I can say that the award has not only encouraged me and my employees and has increased our self-confidence to fight the competition," said the winner of last year's competition.
At the beginning of the history of the company Farmet there was a desire to do something useful.
And so when the state proposed to Karel Zdrasky's father to rent the small workshop as compensation after the confiscation of property by the communists, he did not hesitate long, refused a career in a firm where he worked at the time, and created a company with a few comrades in his father's entourage for the manufacture of plastic bathtubs.
Not long after they began to specialize in presses for vegetable oil.
After eighteen years, it became the largest manufacturer of automatic presses in Central Europe.
The company was known even in the non-specialized public after the success of the contest through the media.
“Not only have our customers started to really get to know the Farmet brand better, but also the foreign partners who have started to realize that they are collaborating with a company that has achieved the greatest success in its home country,” says Karel Zdarsky.
But the past year did not pass at Farmet only in the euphoria of victory.
The company's assessment was based on the economic results of 2008 and part of 2009.
And in 2009 it was the most difficult year for the sale of engineering machines.
At the height of the crisis, which did not really affect citizens, companies were forced to stop their investment projects and begin to limit their purchases of new materials and technologies.
"Obviously, we have not escaped this situation."
“Turnover fell by 40 percent, and we had to limit our production and even lay off,” says Karel Zdarsky.
A viable society must know that from time to time unpopular measures must be taken.
But they managed the situation correctly and retained beneficial results even if they were inferior to those they had before the crisis.
However, at Farmet, they continued without compromise to invest in research and development.
"We have built with the endowments a training and research center, strengthened the company's presentation in international exhibitions and won major awards in national exhibitions," says Zdarsky.
Everything makes us think that the crisis is behind them.
The number of employees goes up, and with them the number of employees as well.
"To the new winner I wish this pleasant feeling of victory but in a calm atmosphere," says Karel Zdarsky.
